<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7079&amp;p=30334#p30334"><![CDATA[
It is working on windows 10, but you won't like the fix I found.  I went to a Windows 7 Ultimate 64 bit laptop that had Classic Shell 4.3.0 running perfectly and created two backup files.  I loaded the main backup into the windows 10 anniversary classic shell 4.3.0.  It didn't work at all.   The settings file from the Window 7 machine did not create the same settings on the windows 10 machine.  On windows 7 the left click opened the classic shell menu and on windows 10 it was set to open the windows start menu.  <br /><br />The original install of Classic Shell on windows 10 anniversary had both start buttons active.  With the upload of the windows 7 menu file into windows 10, only the Classic Shell button is active.  It seems the windows 10 64 bit install is different than the windows 7 64 bit install and the backup files do not align.<br /><br />It is working perfectly on the Windows 10 machine now.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=16168">SysEngineer</a> — Sun Nov 13, 2016 12:21 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
